{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"The magical moment, the magical moment of conducting."},{"time":5000,"text":"Which is, you go onto a stage. There is an orchestra sitting."},{"time":7000,"text":"They are all, you know, warming up and doing stuff."},{"time":11000,"text":"And I go on the podium."},{"time":13000,"text":"You know, this little office of the conductor."},{"time":16000,"text":"Or rather a cubicle, an open-space cubicle,"},{"time":19000,"text":"with a lot of space."},{"time":21000,"text":"And in front of all that noise,"},{"time":23000,"text":"you do a very small gesture."},{"time":25000,"text":"Something like this, not very pomp, not very sophisticated, this."},{"time":29000,"text":"And suddenly, out of the chaos, order."},{"time":32000,"text":"Noise becomes music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"And this is fantastic. And it's so tempting"},{"time":36000,"text":"to think that it's all about me."},{"time":38000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":40000,"text":"All those great people here, virtuosos,"},{"time":42000,"text":"they make noise, they need me to do that."},{"time":44000,"text":"Not really. If it were that,"},{"time":46000,"text":"I would just save you the talk,"},{"time":48000,"text":"and teach you the gesture."},{"time":50000,"text":"So you could go out to the world"},{"time":52000,"text":"and do this thing in whatever company or whatever you want,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and you have perfect harmony. It doesn't work."},{"time":57000,"text":"Let's look at the first video."},{"time":59000,"text":"I hope you'll think it's a good example of harmony."},{"time":62000,"text":"And then speak a little bit about how it comes about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"Was that nice?"},{"time":124000,"text":"So that was a sort of a success."},{"time":127000,"text":"Now, who should we thank for the success?"},{"time":130000,"text":"I mean, obviously the orchestra musicians"},{"time":132000,"text":"playing beautifully,"},{"time":134000,"text":"the Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra."},{"time":138000,"text":"They don't often even look at the conductor."},{"time":140000,"text":"Then you have the clapping audience, yeah,"},{"time":143000,"text":"actually taking part in doing the music."},{"time":145000,"text":"You know Viennese audiences usually don't interfere with the music."},{"time":149000,"text":"This is the closest to an Oriental bellydancing feast"},{"time":153000,"text":"that you will ever get in Vienna."},{"time":155000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"Unlike, for example Israel, where audiences cough all the time."},{"time":159000,"text":"You know, Arthur Rubinstein, the pianist, used to say"},{"time":162000,"text":"that, \"Anywhere in the world, people that have the flu, they go to the doctor."},{"time":165000,"text":"In Tel Aviv they come to my concerts.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":169000,"text":"So that's a sort of a tradition."},{"time":171000,"text":"But Viennese audiences do not do that."},{"time":173000,"text":"Here they go out of their regular, just to be part of that,"},{"time":178000,"text":"to become part of the orchestra, and that's great."},{"time":180000,"text":"You know, audiences like you, yeah,"},{"time":182000,"text":"make the event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"But what about the conductor? What can you say"},{"time":187000,"text":"the conductor was doing, actually?"},{"time":191000,"text":"Um, he was happy."},{"time":194000,"text":"And I often show this to senior management."},{"time":197000,"text":"People get annoyed."},{"time":199000,"text":"\"You come to work. How come you're so happy?\""},{"time":201000,"text":"Something must be wrong there, yeah? But he's spreading happiness."},{"time":204000,"text":"And I think the happiness, the important thing is this happiness"},{"time":206000,"text":"does not come from"},{"time":209000,"text":"only his own story and his joy of the music."},{"time":212000,"text":"The joy is about enabling other people's stories"},{"time":216000,"text":"to be heard at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"You have the story of the orchestra as a professional body."},{"time":222000,"text":"You have the story of the audience as a community. Yeah."},{"time":225000,"text":"You have the stories of the individuals"},{"time":227000,"text":"in the orchestra and in the audience."},{"time":229000,"text":"And then you have other stories, unseen."},{"time":232000,"text":"People who build this wonderful concert hall."},{"time":235000,"text":"People who made those Stradivarius, Amati, all those beautiful instruments."},{"time":240000,"text":"And all those stories are being heard at the same time."},{"time":243000,"text":"This is the true experience of a live concert."},{"time":246000,"text":"That's a reason to go out of home. Yeah?"},{"time":248000,"text":"And not all conductors do just that."},{"time":251000,"text":"Let's see somebody else, a great conductor."},{"time":253000,"text":"Riccardo Muti, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"Yeah, that was very short, but you could see"},{"time":294000,"text":"it's a completely different figure. Right?"},{"time":296000,"text":"He's awesome. He's so commanding. Yeah?"},{"time":298000,"text":"So clear. Maybe a little bit over-clear."},{"time":303000,"text":"Can we have a little demonstration? Would you be my orchestra for a second?"},{"time":306000,"text":"Can you sing, please, the first note of Don Giovanni?"},{"time":308000,"text":"You have to sing \"Aaaaaah,\" and I'll stop you."},{"time":311000,"text":"Okay? Ready?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"Audience: ♫ Aaaaaaah ... ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Itay Talgam: Come on, with me. If you do it without me"},{"time":317000,"text":"I feel even more redundant than I already feel."},{"time":320000,"text":"So please, wait for the conductor."},{"time":323000,"text":"Now look at me. \"Aaaaaah,\" and I stop you. Let's go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"Audience: ♫ ... Aaaaaaaah ... ♫"},{"time":330000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"Itay Talgam: So we'll have a little chat later."},{"time":334000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":335000,"text":"But ... There is a vacancy for a ..."},{"time":339000,"text":"But -- (Laughter)"},{"time":343000,"text":"-- you could see that you could stop an orchestra with a finger."},{"time":346000,"text":"Now what does Riccardo Muti do? He does something like this ..."},{"time":351000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":352000,"text":"And then -- sort of -- (Laughter)"},{"time":355000,"text":"So not only the instruction is clear,"},{"time":358000,"text":"but also the sanction, what will happen if you don't do what I tell you."},{"time":361000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":364000,"text":"So, does it work? Yes, it works --"},{"time":368000,"text":"to a certain point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"When Muti is asked, \"Why do you conduct like this?\""},{"time":372000,"text":"He says, \"I'm responsible.\""},{"time":374000,"text":"Responsible in front of him."},{"time":376000,"text":"No he doesn't really mean Him. He means Mozart,"},{"time":378000,"text":"which is -- (Laughter) -- like a third seat from the center."},{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":383000,"text":"So he says, \"If I'm --"},{"time":385000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":387000,"text":"if I'm responsible for Mozart,"},{"time":389000,"text":"this is going to be the only story to be told."},{"time":391000,"text":"It's Mozart as I, Riccardo Muti, understand it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"And you know what happened to Muti?"},{"time":397000,"text":"Three years ago he got a letter signed by"},{"time":399000,"text":"all 700 employees of La Scala,"},{"time":402000,"text":"musical employees, I mean the musicians,"},{"time":404000,"text":"saying, \"You're a great conductor. We don't want to work with you. Please resign.\""},{"time":408000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":409000,"text":"\"Why? Because you don't let us develop."},{"time":412000,"text":"You're using us as instruments, not as partners."},{"time":415000,"text":"And our joy of music, etc., etc. ...\""},{"time":417000,"text":"So he had to resign. Isn't that nice?"},{"time":419000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":421000,"text":"He's a nice guy. He's a really nice guy."},{"time":424000,"text":"Well, can you do it with less control,"},{"time":427000,"text":"or with a different kind of control?"},{"time":429000,"text":"Let's look at the next conductor, Richard Strauss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"I'm afraid you'll get the feeling that I really picked on him because he's old."},{"time":467000,"text":"It's not true. When he was a young man"},{"time":470000,"text":"of about 30, he wrote what he called"},{"time":472000,"text":"\"The Ten Commandments for Conductors.\""},{"time":474000,"text":"The first one was: If you sweat by the end of the concert"},{"time":477000,"text":"it means that you must have done something wrong."},{"time":479000,"text":"That's the first one. The fourth one you'll like better."},{"time":481000,"text":"It says: Never look at the trombones --"},{"time":483000,"text":"it only encourages them."},{"time":485000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"So, the whole idea is really to let"},{"time":492000,"text":"it happen by itself."},{"time":494000,"text":"Do not interfere."},{"time":496000,"text":"But how does it happen? Did you see"},{"time":499000,"text":"him turning pages in the score?"},{"time":501000,"text":"Now, either he is senile,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and doesn't remember his own music, because he wrote the music."},{"time":506000,"text":"Or he is actually transferring a very strong message to them, saying,"},{"time":509000,"text":"\"Come on guys. You have to play by the book."},{"time":513000,"text":"So it's not about my story. It's not about your story."},{"time":515000,"text":"It's only the execution of the written music,"},{"time":518000,"text":"no interpretation.\""},{"time":520000,"text":"Interpretation is the real story of the performer."},{"time":523000,"text":"So, no, he doesn't want that. That's a different kind of control."},{"time":526000,"text":"Let's see another super-conductor,"},{"time":529000,"text":"a German super-conductor. Herbert von Karajan, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"What's different? Did you see the eyes? Closed."},{"time":568000,"text":"Did you see the hands?"},{"time":571000,"text":"Did you see this kind of movement? Let me conduct you. Twice."},{"time":574000,"text":"Once like a Muti, and you'll -- (Claps) -- clap, just once."},{"time":576000,"text":"And then like Karajan. Let's see what happens. Okay?"},{"time":578000,"text":"Like Muti. You ready? Because Muti ..."},{"time":581000,"text":"(Laughter) Okay? Ready? Let's do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Audience: (Claps)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"Itay Talgam: Hmm ... again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"Audience: (Claps)"},{"time":589000,"text":"Itay Talgam: Good. Now like a Karajan. Since you're already trained,"},{"time":591000,"text":"let me concentrate, close my eyes. Come, come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"Audience: (Claps) (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"Itay Talgam: Why not together? (Laughter)"},{"time":600000,"text":"Because you didn't know when to play."},{"time":602000,"text":"Now I can tell you, even the Berlin Philharmonic"},{"time":604000,"text":"doesn't know when to play."},{"time":606000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":607000,"text":"But I'll tell you how they do it. No cynicism."},{"time":609000,"text":"This is a German orchestra, yes?"},{"time":611000,"text":"They look at Karajan. And then they look at each other."},{"time":615000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":618000,"text":"\"Do you understand what this guy wants?\""},{"time":621000,"text":"And after doing that,"},{"time":623000,"text":"they really look at each other, and the first players of the orchestra"},{"time":625000,"text":"lead the whole ensemble in playing together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"And when Karajan is asked about it"},{"time":630000,"text":"he actually says, \"Yes, the worst damage"},{"time":632000,"text":"I can do to my orchestra"},{"time":634000,"text":"is to give them a clear instruction."},{"time":638000,"text":"Because that would"},{"time":640000,"text":"prevent the ensemble, the listening to each other"},{"time":644000,"text":"that is needed for an orchestra.\""},{"time":646000,"text":"Now that's great. What about the eyes?"},{"time":648000,"text":"Why are the eyes closed?"},{"time":650000,"text":"There is a wonderful story about Karajan conducting in London."},{"time":654000,"text":"And he cues in a flute player like this."},{"time":657000,"text":"The guy has no idea what to do. (Laughter)"},{"time":660000,"text":"\"Maestro, with all due respect, when should I start?\""},{"time":663000,"text":"What do you think Karajan's reply was? When should I start?"},{"time":666000,"text":"Oh yeah. He says, \"You start when you can't stand it anymore.\""},{"time":670000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"Meaning that you know you have no authority to change anything."},{"time":678000,"text":"It's my music. The real music is only in Karajan's head."},{"time":682000,"text":"And you have to guess my mind. So you are under tremendous pressure"},{"time":685000,"text":"because I don't give you instruction,"},{"time":687000,"text":"and yet, you have to guess my mind."},{"time":689000,"text":"So it's a different kind of, a very spiritual but yet"},{"time":691000,"text":"very firm control."},{"time":694000,"text":"Can we do it in another way? Of course we can. Let's go back"},{"time":696000,"text":"to the first conductor we've seen:"},{"time":698000,"text":"Carlos Kleiber, his name. Next video, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"(Laughter) Yeah."},{"time":760000,"text":"Well, it is different. But isn't that controlling in the same way?"},{"time":763000,"text":"No, it's not, because he is not telling them what to do."},{"time":766000,"text":"When he does this, it's not,"},{"time":768000,"text":"\"Take your Stradivarius and like Jimi Hendrix,"},{"time":771000,"text":"smash it on the floor.\" It's not that."},{"time":773000,"text":"He says, \"This is the gesture of the music."},{"time":775000,"text":"I'm opening a space for you"},{"time":777000,"text":"to put in another layer"},{"time":779000,"text":"of interpretation.\""},{"time":781000,"text":"That is another story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"But how does it really work together"},{"time":785000,"text":"if it doesn't give them instructions?"},{"time":787000,"text":"It's like being on a rollercoaster. Yeah?"},{"time":789000,"text":"You're not really given any instructions,"},{"time":791000,"text":"but the forces of the process itself keep you in place."},{"time":795000,"text":"That's what he does."},{"time":797000,"text":"The interesting thing is of course the rollercoaster does not really exist."},{"time":799000,"text":"It's not a physical thing. It's in the players' heads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"And that's what makes them into partners."},{"time":806000,"text":"You have the plan in your head."},{"time":808000,"text":"You know what to do, even though Kleiber is not conducting you."},{"time":811000,"text":"But here and there and that. You know what to do."},{"time":814000,"text":"And you become a partner building the rollercoaster,"},{"time":817000,"text":"yeah, with sound,"},{"time":819000,"text":"as you actually take the ride."},{"time":821000,"text":"This is very exciting for those players."},{"time":824000,"text":"They do need to go to a sanatorium for two weeks, later."},{"time":826000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":827000,"text":"It is very tiring. Yeah?"},{"time":829000,"text":"But it's the best music making, like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"But of course it's not only about motivation"},{"time":836000,"text":"and giving them a lot of physical energy."},{"time":839000,"text":"You also have to be very professional."},{"time":841000,"text":"And look again at this Kleiber."},{"time":843000,"text":"Can we have the next video, quickly?"},{"time":845000,"text":"You'll see what happens when there is a mistake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"(Music) Again you see the beautiful body language."},{"time":852000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":858000,"text":"And now there is a trumpet player who"},{"time":861000,"text":"does something not exactly the way it should be done."},{"time":863000,"text":"Go along with the video. Look."},{"time":868000,"text":"See, second time for the same player."},{"time":874000,"text":"(Laughter) And now the third time for the same player."},{"time":881000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":882000,"text":"\"Wait for me after the concert."},{"time":884000,"text":"I have a short notice to give you.\""},{"time":886000,"text":"You know, when it's needed, the authority is there. It's very important."},{"time":890000,"text":"But authority is not enough to make people your partners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893000,"text":"Let's see the next video, please. See what happens here."},{"time":895000,"text":"You might be surprised having seen Kleiber"},{"time":897000,"text":"as such a hyperactive guy."},{"time":900000,"text":"He's conducting Mozart."},{"time":902000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":905000,"text":"The whole orchestra is playing."},{"time":907000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":909000,"text":"Now something else."},{"time":911000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":921000,"text":"See? He is there 100 percent,"},{"time":925000,"text":"but not commanding, not telling what to do."},{"time":927000,"text":"Rather enjoying what the soloist is doing."},{"time":930000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"Another solo now. See what you can pick up from this."},{"time":936000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":942000,"text":"Look at the eyes."},{"time":948000,"text":"Okay. You see that?"},{"time":950000,"text":"First of all, it's a kind of a compliment we all like to get."},{"time":953000,"text":"It's not feedback. It's an \"Mmmm ...\" Yeah, it comes from here."},{"time":956000,"text":"So that's a good thing."},{"time":958000,"text":"And the second thing is"},{"time":960000,"text":"it's about actually being in control,"},{"time":962000,"text":"but in a very special way."},{"time":964000,"text":"When Kleiber does -- did you see the eyes,"},{"time":967000,"text":"going from here? (Singing)"},{"time":969000,"text":"You know what happens? Gravitation is no more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973000,"text":"Kleiber not only creates a process,"},{"time":975000,"text":"but also creates the conditions in the world"},{"time":978000,"text":"in which this process takes place."},{"time":981000,"text":"So again, the oboe player"},{"time":983000,"text":"is completely autonomous"},{"time":985000,"text":"and therefore happy and proud of his work,"},{"time":988000,"text":"and creative and all of that."},{"time":990000,"text":"And the level in which Kleiber is in control is in a different level."},{"time":994000,"text":"So control is no longer a zero-sum game."},{"time":997000,"text":"You have this control. You have this control. And all you put together,"},{"time":999000,"text":"in partnership, brings about the best music."},{"time":1003000,"text":"So Kleiber is about process."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Kleiber is about conditions in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"But you need to have process and content to create the meaning."},{"time":1011000,"text":"Lenny Bernstein, my own personal maestro."},{"time":1013000,"text":"Since he was a great teacher,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"Lenny Bernstein always started from the meaning. Look at this, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081000,"text":"Do you remember the face of Muti, at the beginning?"},{"time":1083000,"text":"Well he had a wonderful expression, but only one."},{"time":1086000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1087000,"text":"Did you see Lenny's face?"},{"time":1089000,"text":"You know why? Because the meaning of the music is pain."},{"time":1093000,"text":"And you're playing a painful sound."},{"time":1095000,"text":"And you look at Lenny and he's suffering."},{"time":1098000,"text":"But not in a way that you want to stop."},{"time":1100000,"text":"It's suffering, like, enjoying himself in a Jewish way, as they say."},{"time":1104000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1108000,"text":"But you can see the music on his face."},{"time":1111000,"text":"You can see the baton left his hand. No more baton."},{"time":1114000,"text":"Now it's about you, the player,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"telling the story."},{"time":1118000,"text":"Now it's a reversed thing. You're telling the story. And you're telling the story."},{"time":1120000,"text":"And even briefly, you become the storyteller"},{"time":1123000,"text":"to which the community, the whole community, listens to."},{"time":1126000,"text":"And Bernstein enables that. Isn't that wonderful?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"Now, if you are doing all the things we talked about, together,"},{"time":1134000,"text":"and maybe some others,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"you can get to this wonderful point of doing without doing."},{"time":1139000,"text":"And for the last video, I think this is simply the best title."},{"time":1144000,"text":"My friend Peter says,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"\"If you love something, give it away.\" So, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1214000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}